It’s the most significant NFL day in New York since … The Jets decided to start over with Zach Wilson instead of Sam Darnold on April 29, 2021? Eli Manning’s retirement on Jan. 24, 2020? The Giants’ playoff game on Jan. 8, 2017? The Giants’ last Super Bowl appearance on Feb. 5, 2012? No matter your answer, New York gets a respite Thursday from how the Jets and Giants are tied for the worst record in the NFL over the past five years (22-59). The focus instead will be on how each team has two picks in the top 10 of the NFL Draft and can begin to turn around its future. Here are six mini-mock drafts showing how those first 10 picks could play out in different scenarios, based on evaluations and information-gathering from sources around the league: